President Obama called Governor Barbour of Mississippi to express his concern for the well-being of the people of Mississippi following severe tornado activity over the weekend. The President offered his condolences for the loss of life and assured the Governor that they would have everything they needed to respond to the tragedy. FEMA teams are currently on the ground assessing the damage. The President and the Governor also discussed the response to the Deepwater Horizon drilling unit and the President reassured the Governor that efforts were being made to contain and minimize the environmental impact of the oil sheen offshore.